                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <head>No. 119.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wing</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito, Ecuador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-02-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 27, 1872</date>. (Received April
                        15.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 200.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that the 22d of
                    February received the considerate attention of this government.</p>
                <p>The bands of the government were sent to serenade this legation. Not only the
                    diplomatic agents and government officials paid visits to my house, but many
                    prominent private citizens called to offer their compliments upon that day.</p>
                <pb facs="0274" n="178" xml:id="pg_178"/>
                <p>President Moreno was quite unwell, but sent his staff officers with Minister
                    Leon, who presented his greetings, together with the most kindly sentiments
                    toward President Grant and yourself. I merely mention this matter in order that
                    you may appreciate how cordial and sincere an interest this people seem to
                    evince in all things pertaining to the history and honor of the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>RUMSEY WING.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
